{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionThe advancement in computational power has led to enhanced capabilities of large language models in accurately identifying the focal points within citation networks [1,13], as well as in conducting intelligent analyses of big data [2,3].",
    "The text representation method, drawing inspiration from the quantum density matrix, has found application in various downstream NLP tasks, including graphic-text matching [21], sentiment analysis [44], and abstract extraction [42].",
    "Large language models heavily depend on training sets to acquire semantic information.",
    "However, text representation rooted in the quantum density matrix treats words as distinct entities and disregards the semantic connections existing between them.",
    "Considering the inherent vagueness of natural language, the comprehension of language must account for elements such as contextual nuances and the positioning of phrases."
  ]
}